52// Additional flags and pointers that need to be stored with each message type
53struct ubxAutomaticFlags
54{
55 union {
56 uint8_t all;
57 struct
58 {
59 uint8_t automatic : 1; // Will this message be delivered and parsed "automatically" (without polling)
60 uint8_t implicitUpdate : 1; // Is the update triggered by accessing stale data (=true) or by a call to
61 // checkUblox (=false)
62 uint8_t addToFileBuffer : 1; // Should the raw UBX data be added to the file buffer?
63 uint8_t callbackCopyValid : 1; // Is the copy of the data struct used by the callback valid/fresh?
64 } bits;
65 } flags;
66};

72
73typedef struct
74{
75 uint32_t iTOW; // GPS time of week of the navigation epoch: ms
76 int32_t ecefX; // ECEF X coordinate: cm
77 int32_t ecefY; // ECEF Y coordinate: cm
78 int32_t ecefZ; // ECEF Z coordinate: cm
79 uint32_t pAcc; // Position Accuracy Estimate: cm
80} UBX_NAV_POSECEF_data_t;

89

92 uint32_t ecefY : 1;
93 uint32_t ecefZ : 1;
94 uint32_t pAcc : 1;
95 } bits;
96 } moduleQueried;
97} UBX_NAV_POSECEF_moduleQueried_t;

150// UBX-NAV-STATUS (0x01 0x03): Receiver navigation status
151const uint16_t UBX_NAV_STATUS_LEN = 16;
152
153typedef struct
154{
155 uint32_t iTOW; // GPS time of week of the navigation epoch: ms
156 uint8_t gpsFix; // GPSfix Type: 0x00 = no fix; 0x01 = dead reckoning only; 0x02 = 2D-fix; 0x03 = 3D-fix
157 // 0x04 = GPS + dead reckoning combined; 0x05 = Time only fix; 0x06..0xff = reserved
158 union {
159 uint8_t all;
160 struct
161 {
162 uint8_t gpsFixOk : 1; // 1 = position and velocity valid and within DOP and ACC Masks.
163 uint8_t diffSoln : 1; // 1 = differential corrections were applied
164 uint8_t wknSet : 1; // 1 = Week Number valid (see Time Validity section for details)
165 uint8_t towSet : 1; // 1 = Time of Week valid (see Time Validity section for details)
166 } bits;
167 } flags;
168 union {
169 uint8_t all;
170 struct
171 {
172 uint8_t diffCorr : 1; // 1 = differential corrections available
173 uint8_t carrSolnValid : 1; // 1 = valid carrSoln
174 uint8_t reserved : 4;
175 uint8_t mapMatching : 2; // map matching status: 00: none
176 // 01: valid but not used, i.e. map matching data was received, but was too old
177 // 10: valid and used, map matching data was applied
178 // 11: valid and used, map matching data was applied.
179 } bits;
180 } fixStat;
181 union {
182 uint8_t all;
183 struct
184 {
185 uint8_t psmState : 2; // power save mode state
186 // 0: ACQUISITION [or when psm disabled]
187 // 1: TRACKING
188 // 2: POWER OPTIMIZED TRACKING
189 // 3: INACTIVE
190 uint8_t reserved1 : 1;
191 uint8_t spoofDetState : 2; // Spoofing detection state
192 // 0: Unknown or deactivated
193 // 1: No spoofing indicated
194 // 2: Spoofing indicated
195 // 3: Multiple spoofing indications
196 uint8_t reserved2 : 1;
197 uint8_t carrSoln : 2; // Carrier phase range solution status:
198 // 0: no carrier phase range solution
199 // 1: carrier phase range solution with floating ambiguities
200 // 2: carrier phase range solution with fixed ambiguities
201 } bits;
202 } flags2;
203 uint32_t ttff; // Time to first fix (millisecond time tag): ms
204 uint32_t msss; // Milliseconds since Startup / Reset: ms
205} UBX_NAV_STATUS_data_t;
206
207typedef struct
208{
209 union {
210 uint32_t all;
211 struct
212 {
213 uint32_t all : 1;
214
215 uint32_t iTOW : 1;
216 uint32_t gpsFix : 1;
217
218 uint32_t gpsFixOk : 1;
219 uint32_t diffSoln : 1;
220 uint32_t wknSet : 1;
221 uint32_t towSet : 1;
222
223 uint32_t diffCorr : 1;
224 uint32_t carrSolnValid : 1;
225 uint32_t mapMatching : 1;
226
227 uint32_t psmState : 1;
228 uint32_t spoofDetState : 1;
229 uint32_t carrSoln : 1;
230
231 uint32_t ttff : 1;
232 uint32_t msss : 1;
233 } bits;
234 } moduleQueried;
235} UBX_NAV_STATUS_moduleQueried_t;
236

243 UBX_NAV_STATUS_data_t *callbackData;
244} UBX_NAV_STATUS_t;

290// UBX-NAV-ATT (0x01 0x05): Attitude solution
291const uint16_t UBX_NAV_ATT_LEN = 32;
292
293typedef struct
294{
295 uint32_t iTOW; // GPS time of week of the navigation epoch: ms
296 uint8_t version; // Message version (0x00 for this version)
297 uint8_t reserved1[3];
298 int32_t roll; // Vehicle roll: Degrees * 1e-5
299 int32_t pitch; // Vehicle pitch: Degrees * 1e-5
300 int32_t heading; // Vehicle heading: Degrees * 1e-5
301 uint32_t accRoll; // Vehicle roll accuracy (if null, roll angle is not available): Degrees * 1e-5
302 uint32_t accPitch; // Vehicle pitch accuracy (if null, roll angle is not available): Degrees * 1e-5
303 uint32_t accHeading; // Vehicle heading accuracy (if null, roll angle is not available): Degrees * 1e-5
304} UBX_NAV_ATT_data_t;

335// UBX-NAV-PVT (0x01 0x07): Navigation position velocity time solution
336const uint16_t UBX_NAV_PVT_LEN = 92;
337
338typedef struct
339{
340 uint32_t iTOW; // GPS time of week of the navigation epoch: ms
341 uint16_t year; // Year (UTC)
342 uint8_t month; // Month, range 1..12 (UTC)
343 uint8_t day; // Day of month, range 1..31 (UTC)
344 uint8_t hour; // Hour of day, range 0..23 (UTC)
345 uint8_t min; // Minute of hour, range 0..59 (UTC)
346 uint8_t sec; // Seconds of minute, range 0..60 (UTC)
347 union {
348 uint8_t all;
349 struct
350 {
351 uint8_t validDate : 1; // 1 = valid UTC Date
352 uint8_t validTime : 1; // 1 = valid UTC time of day
353 uint8_t fullyResolved : 1; // 1 = UTC time of day has been fully resolved (no seconds uncertainty).
354 uint8_t validMag : 1; // 1 = valid magnetic declination
355 } bits;
356 } valid;
357 uint32_t tAcc; // Time accuracy estimate (UTC): ns
358 int32_t nano; // Fraction of second, range -1e9 .. 1e9 (UTC): ns
359 uint8_t fixType; // GNSSfix Type:
360 // 0: no fix
361 // 1: dead reckoning only
362 // 2: 2D-fix
363 // 3: 3D-fix
364 // 4: GNSS + dead reckoning combined
365 // 5: time only fix
366 union {
367 uint8_t all;
368 struct
369 {
370 uint8_t gnssFixOK : 1; // 1 = valid fix (i.e within DOP & accuracy masks)
371 uint8_t diffSoln : 1; // 1 = differential corrections were applied
372 uint8_t psmState : 3;
373 uint8_t
374 headVehValid : 1; // 1 = heading of vehicle is valid, only set if the receiver is in sensor fusion mode
375 uint8_t carrSoln : 2; // Carrier phase range solution status:
376 // 0: no carrier phase range solution
377 // 1: carrier phase range solution with floating ambiguities
378 // 2: carrier phase range solution with fixed ambiguities
379 } bits;
380 } flags;
381 union {
382 uint8_t all;
383 struct
384 {
385 uint8_t reserved : 5;
386 uint8_t
387 confirmedAvai : 1; // 1 = information about UTC Date and Time of Day validity confirmation is available
388 uint8_t confirmedDate : 1; // 1 = UTC Date validity could be confirmed
389 uint8_t confirmedTime : 1; // 1 = UTC Time of Day could be confirmed
390 } bits;
391 } flags2;
392 uint8_t numSV; // Number of satellites used in Nav Solution
393 int32_t lon; // Longitude: deg * 1e-7
394 int32_t lat; // Latitude: deg * 1e-7
395 int32_t height; // Height above ellipsoid: mm
396 int32_t hMSL; // Height above mean sea level: mm
397 uint32_t hAcc; // Horizontal accuracy estimate: mm
398 uint32_t vAcc; // Vertical accuracy estimate: mm
399 int32_t velN; // NED north velocity: mm/s
400 int32_t velE; // NED east velocity: mm/s
401 int32_t velD; // NED down velocity: mm/s
402 int32_t gSpeed; // Ground Speed (2-D): mm/s
403 int32_t headMot; // Heading of motion (2-D): deg * 1e-5
404 uint32_t sAcc; // Speed accuracy estimate: mm/s
405 uint32_t headAcc; // Heading accuracy estimate (both motion and vehicle): deg * 1e-5
406 uint16_t pDOP; // Position DOP * 0.01
407 union {
408 uint8_t all;
409 struct
410 {
411 uint8_t invalidLlh : 1; // 1 = Invalid lon, lat, height and hMSL
412 } bits;
413 } flags3;
414 uint8_t reserved1[5];
415 int32_t headVeh; // Heading of vehicle (2-D): deg * 1e-5
416 int16_t magDec; // Magnetic declination: deg * 1e-2
417 uint16_t magAcc; // Magnetic declination accuracy: deg * 1e-2
418} UBX_NAV_PVT_data_t;
419

421{
422 union {
423 uint32_t all;
424 struct

426 uint32_t all : 1;
427

617// UBX-NAV-HPPOSECEF (0x01 0x13): High precision position solution in ECEF
618const uint16_t UBX_NAV_HPPOSECEF_LEN = 28;
619
620typedef struct
621{
622 uint8_t version; // Message version (0x00 for this version)
623 uint8_t reserved1[3];
624 uint32_t iTOW; // GPS time of week of the navigation epoch: ms
625 int32_t ecefX; // ECEF X coordinate: cm
626 int32_t ecefY; // ECEF Y coordinate: cm
627 int32_t ecefZ; // ECEF Z coordinate: cm
628 int8_t ecefXHp; // High precision component of ECEF X coordinate: mm * 0.1
629 int8_t ecefYHp; // High precision component of ECEF Y coordinate: mm * 0.1
630 int8_t ecefZHp; // High precision component of ECEF Z coordinate: mm * 0.1
631 union {
632 uint8_t all;
633 struct
634 {
635 uint8_t invalidEcef : 1; // 1 = Invalid ecefX, ecefY, ecefZ, ecefXHp, ecefYHp and ecefZHp
636 } bits;
637 } flags;
638 uint32_t pAcc; // Position Accuracy Estimate: mm * 0.1

782 // fusion mode

817 uint16_t accPitch; // Vehicle pitch accuracy (if null, pitch angle is not available): 1e-2 deg
818 uint16_t accHeading; // Vehicle heading accuracy (if null, heading angle is not available): 1e-2 deg

1080typedef struct

1099 // navigation

1108 // 5, 6, 7: other orbit information is used

1110 uint32_t almAvail : 1; // 1 = almanac is available for this SV

1117 // Signal Identifiers
1118 uint32_t slasCorrUsed : 1; // 1 = QZSS SLAS corrections have been used for a signal in the subset specified
1119 // in Signal Identifiers
1120 uint32_t spartnCorrUsed : 1; // 1 = SPARTN corrections have been used for a signal in the subset specified
1121 // in Signal Identifiers
1122 uint32_t prCorrUsed : 1; // 1 = Pseudorange corrections have been used for a signal in the subset specified
1123 // in Signal Identifiers
1124 uint32_t crCorrUsed : 1; // 1 = Carrier range corrections have been used for a signal in the subset
1125 // specified in Signal Identifiers
1126 uint32_t doCorrUsed : 1; // 1 = Range rate (Doppler) corrections have been used for a signal in the subset
1127 // specified in Signal Identifiers

1129 } bits;
1130 } flags;

1224 int8_t relPosHPN; // High-precision North component of relative position vector: mm * 0.1
1225 int8_t relPosHPE; // High-precision East component of relative position vector: mm * 0.1
1226 int8_t relPosHPD; // High-precision Down component of relative position vector: mm * 0.1
1227 int8_t relPosHPLength; // High-precision component of the length of the relative position vector: mm * 0.1
1228 uint32_t accN; // Accuracy of relative position North component: mm * 0.1
1229 uint32_t accE; // Accuracy of relative position East component: mm * 0.1
1230 uint32_t accD; // Accuracy of relative position Down component: mm * 0.1
1231 uint32_t accLength; // Accuracy of length of the relative position vector: mm * 0.1
1232 uint32_t accHeading; // Accuracy of heading of the relative position vector: Degrees * 1e-5
1233 uint8_t reserved2[4];
1234 union {
1235 uint32_t all;
1236 struct
1237 {
1238 uint32_t gnssFixOK : 1; // A valid fix (i.e within DOP & accuracy masks)
1239 uint32_t diffSoln : 1; // 1 if differential corrections were applied
1240 uint32_t relPosValid : 1; // 1 if relative position components and accuracies are valid
1241 uint32_t carrSoln : 2; // Carrier phase range solution status:
1242 // 0 = no carrier phase range solution
1243 // 1 = carrier phase range solution with floating ambiguities
1244 // 2 = carrier phase range solution with fixed ambiguities
1245 uint32_t isMoving : 1; // 1 if the receiver is operating in moving baseline mode
1246 uint32_t refPosMiss : 1; // 1 if extrapolated reference position was used to compute moving baseline
1247 // solution this epoch
1248 uint32_t refObsMiss : 1; // 1 if extrapolated reference observations were used to compute moving baseline
1249 // solution this epoch
1250 uint32_t relPosHeadingValid : 1; // 1 if relPosHeading is valid
1251 uint32_t relPosNormalized : 1; // 1 if the components of the relative position vector (including the
1252 // high-precision parts) are normalized
1253 } bits;
1254 } flags;
1255} UBX_NAV_RELPOSNED_data_t;

1508// UBX-CFG-TP5 (0x06 0x31): Time pulse parameters
1509const uint16_t UBX_CFG_TP5_LEN = 32;
1510
1511typedef struct
1512{
1513 uint8_t tpIdx; // Time pulse selection (0 = TIMEPULSE, 1 = TIMEPULSE2)
1514 uint8_t version; // Message version (0x01 for this version)
1515 uint8_t reserved1[2];
1516 int16_t antCableDelay; // Antenna cable delay: ns
1517 int16_t rfGroupDelay; // RF group delay: ns
1518 uint32_t freqPeriod; // Frequency or period time, depending on setting of bit 'isFreq': Hz_or_us
1519 uint32_t freqPeriodLock; // Frequency or period time when locked to GNSS time, only used if 'lockedOtherSet' is set:
1520 // Hz_or_us
1521 uint32_t pulseLenRatio; // Pulse length or duty cycle, depending on 'isLength': us_or_2^-32
1522 uint32_t pulseLenRatioLock; // Pulse length or duty cycle when locked to GNSS time, only used if 'lockedOtherSet' is
1523 // set: us_or_2^-32
1524 int32_t userConfigDelay; // User-configurable time pulse delay: ns
1525 union {
1526 uint32_t all;
1527 struct
1528 {
1529 uint32_t active : 1; // If set enable time pulse; if pin assigned to another function, other function takes
1530 // precedence.
1531 uint32_t lockGnssFreq : 1; // If set, synchronize time pulse to GNSS as soon as GNSS time is valid. If not
1532 // set, or before GNSS time is valid, use local clock.
1533 uint32_t lockedOtherSet : 1; // If set the receiver switches between the timepulse settings given by
1534 // 'freqPeriodLocked' & 'pulseLenLocked' and those given by 'freqPeriod' &
1535 // 'pulseLen'.
1536 uint32_t isFreq : 1; // If set 'freqPeriodLock' and 'freqPeriod' are interpreted as frequency, otherwise
1537 // interpreted as period.
1538 uint32_t isLength : 1; // If set 'pulseLenRatioLock' and 'pulseLenRatio' interpreted as pulse length,
1539 // otherwise interpreted as duty cycle.
1540 uint32_t alignToTow : 1; // Align pulse to top of second (period time must be integer fraction of 1s). Also
1541 // set 'lockGnssFreq' to use this feature.
1542 uint32_t polarity : 1; // Pulse polarity: 0: falling edge at top of second; 1: rising edge at top of second
1543 uint32_t gridUtcGnss : 4; // Timegrid to use: 0: UTC; 1: GPS; 2: GLONASS; 3: BeiDou; 4: Galileo
1544 uint32_t
1545 syncMode : 3; // Sync Manager lock mode to use:
1546 // 0: switch to 'freqPeriodLock' and 'pulseLenRatioLock' as soon as Sync Manager has an
1547 // accurate time, never switch back to 'freqPeriod' and 'pulseLenRatio' 1: switch to
1548 // 'freqPeriodLock' and 'pulseLenRatioLock' as soon as Sync Manager has an accurate time,
1549 // and switch back to 'freqPeriod' and 'pulseLenRatio' as soon as time gets inaccurate
1550 } bits;
1551 } flags;
1552} UBX_CFG_TP5_data_t;
